micro-level, as well as the political supply and the demand-side. More specifically, this study shows that it is necessary to consider both opportunity structures, created by demand and supply-side factors, as well as the ability of the FN to take advantage of the available opportunities. Of particular interest is the author's analysis of the sociology and attitudes of the FN-voters.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aPolitical partieszSweden. 0aPopulismxFrance. 0aPopulismzFrance. 0aPopulismzSweden. 0aRight-wing extremistsxFrance. 0aRight-wing extremistszFrance. 0aRight-wing extremistszSweden. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Nationalism & Patriotism.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782381808?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782381808423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782381808/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK